msgid "LibreNMS Monitoring Server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network and systems administrators almost always need some form of monitoring. This can include graphing bandwidth usage at router end points, monitoring the up/down of services running on various servers, and much, much more. There are many monitoring options out there, but one option that is very good and has many, if not all, of the monitoring components available under one roof, is LibreNMS.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "This document will only get you started with LibreNMS, but we will point you to the project's excellent (and extensive) documentation to get you going further. There are lots of other options for monitoring out there that this author has used before, Nagios and Cacti being two, but LibreNMS offers what those two projects offer individually, in one spot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "While the installation will pretty closely follow the official install instructions found [here](https://docs.librenms.org/Installation/Install-LibreNMS/), we've added some explanation and even some minor changes, which make this procedure preferable to that excellent document.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prerequisites, Assumptions and Conventions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "A server or container (yes, LibreNMS will run in a container, however if you have a lot to monitor, your best bet would be to install on its own hardware) running Rocky Linux. All commands assume a fresh install of Rocky Linux.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assumption: that you are able to execute commands as root or can _sudo_ to do so\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working knowledge of command-line tools, including text editors such as _vi_\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "We are assuming the use of SNMP v2. If you want to use SNMP v3, it is supported by LibreNMS and will work. You'll just need to switch up the SNMP configuration and options on your devices to match up to v3.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "While we have included the SELinux procedure in this document, the container that we are using in the lab does not include it by default. For this reason, the SELinux procedure has **not** been lab tested.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Throughout this document, the examples use the _vi_ editor as mentioned. When the document says to save your changes and exit, this is done with `SHIFT:wq!`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Some trouble-shooting skills, including log monitoring, web testing, and more, are required.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "These commands should be entered as the root user. Before we begin, note that this installation procedure focuses on *httpd*, rather than *nginx*. If you prefer to use the latter, head up to the [Librenms Install Instructions](https://docs.librenms.org/Installation/Install-LibreNMS/) and follow the guide there. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "We are assuming a fresh install, so we need to do a few things with the repositories before we can continue. First, we need to install the EPEL repository (Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install -y epel-release\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "The current version of LibreNMS requires a minimum PHP version of 8.1. The default package in Rocky Linux 9.0 is PHP 8.0, so we will need to enable a third party repository (true for Rocky Linux 8.6 as well) for this newer version. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "We will install the REMI repository for this. The version of the repository you install will depend on the version of Rocky Linux you are running. We are assuming version 9 below, but change this accordingly for the version you are running: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install http://rpms.remirepo.net/enterprise/remi-release-9.rpm\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once both the EPEL and REMI repositories are installed, it's time to install the packages we will need:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install bash-completion cronie fping git httpd ImageMagick mariadb-server mtr net-snmp net-snmp-utils nmap php81-php-fpm php81-php-cli php81-php-common php81-php-curl php81-php-gd php81-php-json php81-php-mbstring php81-php-process php81-php-snmp php81-php-xml php81-php-zip php81-php-mysqlnd python3 python3-PyMySQL python3-redis python3-memcached python3-pip python3-systemd rrdtool unzip wget\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "All of these packages represent some portion of the LibreNMS feature set.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting Up The librenms User"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "To do this, copy and paste (or type) the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "useradd librenms -d /opt/librenms -M -r -s \"$(which bash)\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "With this command, we are setting the default directory for our new user to \"/opt/librenms\" however the \"-M\" option says \"don't create the directory.\" The reason, of course, is that we will be creating it when we install LibreNMS. The \"-r\" says to make this user a system account and the \"-s\" says to set the shell (in this case, to \"bash\")\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download LibreNMS and Set Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "The downloading is all done through git. You may be familiar with the process as it is used for many projects these days. First, switch over to the /opt directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "cd /opt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then clone the repository:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "git clone https://github.com/librenms/librenms.git\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next change permissions for the directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"chown -R librenms:librenms /opt/librenms\n"
"chmod 771 /opt/librenms\n"
"setfacl -d -m g::rwx /opt/librenms/rrd /opt/librenms/logs /opt/librenms/bootstrap/cache/ /opt/librenms/storage/\n"
"setfacl -R -m g::rwx /opt/librenms/rrd /opt/librenms/logs /opt/librenms/bootstrap/cache/ /opt/librenms/storage/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "The _setfacl_ command stands for \"set file access control lists\" and is another way of securing directories and files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install PHP Dependencies As librenms"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:95
#, no-wrap
msgid "All of the above commands were executed as root or _sudo_, but the PHP dependencies within LibreNMS need to be installed as the librenms user. To do this, run:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "su - librenms\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "And then enter the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "./scripts/composer_wrapper.php install --no-dev\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the script is completed, exit back to root:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "Failure Of PHP Dependency Install Workaround"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "LibreNMS documentation says that when you are behind a proxy server, the above procedure may fail. I've found that it can fail for other reasons as well. For this reason, I've added a procedure for installing Composer later in the process. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set Timezone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "We need to make sure that this is set correctly, both for the system and for PHP. You can find a list of valid timezone settings for PHP [here](https://php.net/manual/en/timezones.php). For instance, for the Central timezone, a common entry would be \"America/Chicago\". Let's start by editing the php.ini file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/opt/remi/php81/php.ini\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "Find the `date.timezone` line and modify it. Note that it is remarked out, so remove the \";\" from the beginning of the line and add your timezone after the \"=\" sign. For our Central timezone example we will use:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:126
#, no-wrap
msgid "date.timezone = America/Chicago\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "Save your changes and exit the php.ini file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "We also need to make sure that the system timezone is correct. Again, using our Central timezone as the example, we would do this with:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "timedatectl set-timezone America/Chicago\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "MariaDB Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before we get into the database setup required for LibreNMS, run through the [MariaDB procedure](../database/database_mariadb-server.md) and specifically the section for \"Securing mariadb-server\", and then come back here for these specific settings. The first thing we need to do is modify the mariadb-server.cnf file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/my.cnf.d/mariadb-server.cnf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:147
#, no-wrap
msgid "And add the following lines to the \"[Mysqld]\" section:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:148
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"innodb_file_per_table=1\n"
"lower_case_table_names=0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:154
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then enable and restart the mariadb server:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:155
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"systemctl enable mariadb\n"
"systemctl restart mariadb\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now gain access to mariadb as the root user. Remember to use the password that you created when folloing the \"Securing mariadb-server\" section that you performed above:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "mysql -u root -p\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "The next thing we need to do is make some specific changes for LibreNMS. With the command below, remember to change the password \"password\" to something secure and document what that is in a safe spot, such as a password manager, so that you will have it later. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:170
#, no-wrap
msgid "At the mysql prompt run:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:171
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"CREATE DATABASE librenms CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;\n"
"CREATE USER 'librenms'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';\n"
"GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON librenms.* TO 'librenms'@'localhost';\n"
"FLUSH PRIVILEGES;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you've done this, type \"exit\" to exit back out of mariadb.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:180
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure PHP-FPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "This section is basically unchanged from the official documentation except for the path to the files. First, copy the www.conf:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:184
#, no-wrap
msgid "cp /etc/opt/remi/php81/php-fpm.d/www.conf /etc/opt/remi/php81/php-fpm.d/librenms.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next modify the librenms.conf file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/opt/remi/php81/php-fpm.d/librenms.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change \"[www]\" to [\"librenms]\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change the user and group to \"librenms\":\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:198
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"user = librenms\n"
"group = librenms\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:204
#, no-wrap
msgid "And finally change the \"listen\" line to reflect a unique name:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "listen = /run/php-fpm-librenms.sock\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "Save your changes and exit the file. If this is the only web service that will be running on this machine, feel free to remove the old www.conf file that we copied:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:211
#, no-wrap
msgid "rm -f /etc/opt/remi/php81/php-fpm.d/www.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure Apache"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "Normally, we would use the [Apache sites-enabled](../web/apache-sites-enabled.md) procedure to set up any web services, but in this case, we are just going with the default setup. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:220
#, no-wrap
msgid "Note that if you want to use that procedure, you simply need to place the configuration file in /etc/httpd/sites-available and then follow the procedure to link it to sites-enabled. The default document root, however, would **not** be /var/www/sub-domains/librenms/html, but instead it would be /opt/librenms/html.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "Again, in this case we aren't using that procedure and just going with the default, suggested setup. To do this, start by creating this file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:223
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/httpd/conf.d/librenms.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:228
#, no-wrap
msgid "And placing the following in that file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:229
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<VirtualHost *:80>\n"
"  DocumentRoot /opt/librenms/html/\n"
"  ServerName  librenms.example.com\n"
"\n"
"  AllowEncodedSlashes NoDecode\n"
"  <Directory \"/opt/librenms/html/\">\n"
"    Require all granted\n"
"    AllowOverride All\n"
"    Options FollowSymLinks MultiViews\n"
"  </Directory>\n"
"\n"
"  # Enable http authorization headers\n"
"  <IfModule setenvif_module>\n"
"    SetEnvIfNoCase ^Authorization$ \"(.+)\" HTTP_AUTHORIZATION=$1\n"
"  </IfModule>\n"
"\n"
"  <FilesMatch \".+\\.php$\">\n"
"    SetHandler \"proxy:unix:/run/php-fpm-librenms.sock|fcgi://localhost\"\n"
"  </FilesMatch>\n"
"</VirtualHost>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:253
#, no-wrap
msgid "You should also remove the old default site, welcome.conf:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:254
#, no-wrap
msgid "rm /etc/httpd/conf.d/welcome.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:259
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finally, we need to enable both _httpd_ and _php-fpm_:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:260
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"systemctl enable --now httpd\n"
"systemctl enable --now php81-php-fpm\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: tags
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:265
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/learning_selinux.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "SELinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please note that if you don't plan on using SELinux, skip this and head to the next section. This might also apply to you if you use LibreNMS on a container that does not support SELinux at the container level, or does not include it by default.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:270
#, no-wrap
msgid "To setup everything with SELinux, you'll need an additional package installed:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:271
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install policycoreutils-python-utils\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:275
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure LibreNMS Contexts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:278
#, no-wrap
msgid "You'll need to set the following contexts for LibreNMS to work properly with SELinux:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:279
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"semanage fcontext -a -t httpd_sys_content_t '/opt/librenms/html(/.*)?'\n"
"semanage fcontext -a -t httpd_sys_rw_content_t '/opt/librenms/(logs|rrd|storage)(/.*)?'\n"
"restorecon -RFvv /opt/librenms\n"
"setsebool -P httpd_can_sendmail=1\n"
"setsebool -P httpd_execmem 1\n"
"chcon -t httpd_sys_rw_content_t /opt/librenms/.env\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "Allow fping"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:291
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create a file called `http_fping.tt` anywhere and it will be installed via a command later. The contents of this file are:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:292
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"module http_fping 1.0;\n"
"\n"
"require {\n"
"type httpd_t;\n"
"class capability net_raw;\n"
"class rawip_socket { getopt create setopt write read };\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"#============= httpd_t ==============\n"
"allow httpd_t self:capability net_raw;\n"
"allow httpd_t self:rawip_socket { getopt create setopt write read };\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:307
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now install the contents of this file with the following commands:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:308
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"checkmodule -M -m -o http_fping.mod http_fping.tt\n"
"semodule_package -o http_fping.pp -m http_fping.mod\n"
"semodule -i http_fping.pp\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you run into problems and you suspect it might be due to an SELinux issue, run the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:316
#, no-wrap
msgid "audit2why < /var/log/audit/audit.log\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:320
#, no-wrap
msgid "Firewall Configuration - `firewalld`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "We will include the _firewalld_ instructions from the official documentation. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:325
#, no-wrap
msgid "The command to use for _firewalld_ allow rules are as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:326
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"firewall-cmd --zone public --add-service http --add-service https\n"
"firewall-cmd --permanent --zone public --add-service http --add-service https\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:332
#, no-wrap
msgid "The author has problems with this sort of simplistic _firewalld_ rule set. This rule allows your web services to be open to the world, but is that what you want for a monitoring server? \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:334
#, no-wrap
msgid "I would say that this is usually **not** the case. If you'd like a more granular approach to using _firewalld_, take a look at [this document](../security/firewalld.md) and then make changes to your _firewalld_ rules accordingly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:335
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable Symbolic Link And Tab-Autocomplete For lnms Commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:338
#, no-wrap
msgid "First, we need a symbolic link on our _lnms_ command so that it can be executed from anywhere:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:339
#, no-wrap
msgid "ln -s /opt/librenms/lnms /usr/bin/lnms\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:344
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next, we need to set it up for autocomplete:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:345
#, no-wrap
msgid "cp /opt/librenms/misc/lnms-completion.bash /etc/bash_completion.d/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:349
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure snmpd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:352
#, no-wrap
msgid "_SNMP_ stands for \"Simple Network Management Protocol\" and is used in many monitoring programs for pulling data. In version 2, which we are using here, it involves a \"community string\" which is specific for your environment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:354
#, no-wrap
msgid "You'll need to assign this \"community string\" to your network devices that you want to monitor so that _snmpd_ (the \"d\" here stands for the daemon) will be able to find it. If your network has been in place for some time, you may already have a \"community string\" that you are using.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:356
#, no-wrap
msgid "First, copy the snmp.conf file from LibreNMS:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:357
#, no-wrap
msgid "cp /opt/librenms/snmpd.conf.example /etc/snmp/snmpd.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next, edit this file and change the community string from \"RANDOMSTRINGGOESHERE\" to whatever your community string is or will be. In our example, we are changing it to \"LABone\":\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:363
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:539
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/snmp/snmpd.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:368
#, no-wrap
msgid "And change this line:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:369
#, no-wrap
msgid "com2sec readonly  default         RANDOMSTRINGGOESHERE\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:374
#, no-wrap
msgid "to\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:375
#, no-wrap
msgid "com2sec readonly  default         LABone\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:380
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:513
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now save your changes and exit.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:381
#, no-wrap
msgid "Automating With A Cron Job"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:384
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run the following commands to set up the cron jobs:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:385
#, no-wrap
msgid "cp /opt/librenms/librenms.nonroot.cron /etc/cron.d/librenms\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:390
#, no-wrap
msgid "It's important that the poller has run once, even though there will be nothing to poll, before the web setup procedure is run. It saves a lot of head scratching trying to figure out what is wrong when you get poller errors in the validation section later on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:392
#, no-wrap
msgid "The poller is run by the \"librenms\" user, and while it would be possible to switch to this user and run the cron files, it's really better to let the poller do it on its own, so make sure that at least 5 minutes have passed between this section and the \"Web Setup\" section below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:393
#, no-wrap
msgid "Log Rotation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:396
#, no-wrap
msgid "LibreNMS will create a large set of logs over time. You'll need to setup log rotation for this so that it doesn't eat up too much disk space. To do this, simply run this command now:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:397
#, no-wrap
msgid "cp /opt/librenms/misc/librenms.logrotate /etc/logrotate.d/librenms\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:401
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing Composer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:404
#, no-wrap
msgid "PHP Composer is required for the current installation (mentioned in the earlier procedure). If the install you ran earlier failed, you'll need to do this.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:406
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before we start, we need to link our current version of the `php` binary to a location in the path. Since we used the REMI installation to get the correct version of PHP, it is not installed within the path. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:408
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is easy enough to fix with a symbolic link and will make your life much easier as you go through the remaining steps:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:409
#, no-wrap
msgid "ln -s /opt/remi/php81/root/usr/bin/php /usr/bin/php\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:414
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now go to the [Composer website](https://getcomposer.org/download/) and make sure that the following steps haven't changed. If not, go ahead and run these commands somewhere on the machine (the location isn't important as we will move composer when we are done): \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:415
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"php -r \"copy('https://getcomposer.org/installer', 'composer-setup.php');\"\n"
"php -r \"if (hash_file('sha384', 'composer-setup.php') === '55ce33d7678c5a611085589f1f3ddf8b3c52d662cd01d4ba75c0ee0459970c2200a51f492d557530c71c15d8dba01eae') { echo 'Installer verified'; } else { echo 'Installer corrupt'; unlink('composer-setup.php'); } echo PHP_EOL;\"\n"
"php composer-setup.php\n"
"php -r \"unlink('composer-setup.php');\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:423
#, no-wrap
msgid "Move it to a spot within our path. We are using `/usr/local/bin/` for this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:424
#, no-wrap
msgid "mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:428
#, no-wrap
msgid "Web Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:431
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now that we have all of the components installed and configured, our next step is to finish the installation via the web. In our lab version, we've got no hostname setup so to finish the setup, we need to go to the web server by IP address. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:433
#, no-wrap
msgid "The IP of our lab machine is 192.168.1.140, so we need to navigate to the following address in a web browser to finish the install:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:435
#, no-wrap
msgid "`http://192.168.1.140/librenms`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:437
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assuming all is working correctly, you should be redirected to the pre-install checks. Assuming that these are all marked as green, then we should be able to continue.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:439
#, no-wrap
msgid "![LibreNMS Prechecks](../images/librenms_prechecks.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:441
#, no-wrap
msgid "There are four buttons beneath the LibreNMS logo. The first button on the left is for the pre-checks. Our next button over is for the database. You'll need the password that you set for the database user \"librenms\" earlier in the process.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:443
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you've been following along diligently, then you've got that saved in a safe place. Go ahead and click on the \"Database\" button. The \"User\" and \"Password\" should be all that is necessary to fill in here. Once you do that, click the \"Check Credentials\" button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:445
#, no-wrap
msgid "![LibreNMS Database](../images/librenms_configure_database.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:447
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you click that, if it comes back green, then you are ready to click the \"Build Database\" button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:449
#, no-wrap
msgid "![LibreNMS Database Status](../images/librenms_configure_database_status.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/network/librenms_monitoring_server.md:451
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once that is complete, the third button will be active, which is \"Create Admin User\", so go ahead and click this. You will be prompted for an admin user name. In our lab we are simply going to use \"admin\", and a password for that user.\n"
